               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420613-name-1398" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-1398" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-1398" type="surname" value="LEWIS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420613-name-1398" type="given" value="JOSEPH JOHN"></interp>JOSEPH JOHN LEWIS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a Thames-police inspector. At half-past four o'clock in the morning, on the 25th of May, I was on duty at Dept ford, and I saw the prisoner in a boat—he rowed to the bows of the <hi rend="italic">City if London</hi> steam-boat, took a rope, and pulled it into his boat—I rowed round the vessel, and took him just as he had got the last half-inch into his boat—he dropped his hand and the rope together—he said he hoped I should make it as easy as I could for him, and not mention any thing of his former conduct, unless asked for it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. BALLANTINE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> How far had he got from the vessel? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> He was fast to it—this rope was hooked on to die vessel.</p>
